The CU Up Close Program is an opportunity for law students in their pre-
penultimate year of study to get an exclusive look into life at Clayton Utz,
one of Australia's leading law firms

Our in-person program will support you in building practical skills and
knowledge by providing opportunities to interact with senior leaders, recent
graduates, and discover the many ways you can build your future legal career
with Clayton Utz.

What will you gain from this program?

  * Gain practical skills: Immerse yourself in learning & development sessions design to help you succeed in your studies and early careers. 
  * Network with leaders: Get a glimpse of the day-to-day experiences of Clayton Utz lawyers. 
  * Shape your path: Discover the various career opportunities available to you at Clayton Utz. 

Is this program for you?

  * Enrolled in a Bachelor of Laws or a Juris Doctor at an Australian university 
  * In your pre-penultimate year of study (i.e., 1st, 2nd, 3rd year of study in undergraduate or 1st year of Juris Doctor) 
  * A passion for law, genuine curiosity, and an open mind. 

How can I apply?

To apply, you will fill out a short application form and highlight your work
experience and education. Please refer to our application dates. Relevant
location links and apply now information will be updated shortly.

